\begin_layout Standard
Mawacin's phonology phas a very different feel from that of Ludhisyn, although
 this fact is due much more to Ludhisyn's ideosyncratic syncope and usage
 of dental fricatives.
 Mawacin, like other Eastern Sakasic languages, have no trace of any vowel
 harmony in their phonology (unlike Western languages like Sagazdan, which
 preserves highly regular harmony, or Central languages like Ludhisyn which
 reflect traces of vowel harmony).
 
\end_layout

