\begin_layout Subsection
Mood
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mood suffixes go after all finite conjugations, but before any nonfinite
 conjugations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Conditional
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The conditional mood denotes situations that are dependent on something
 happening.
 It's thus often used with a dependent verb phrase which is in the provisional
 form (see §TODO).
 The suffix is 
\emph on
-nu
\emph default
.
 
\end_layout

